Action, I think, was important, and then an L was life.

24:08.269 --> 24:10.092
I am crucified with Christ.

24:10.232 --> 24:12.616
Nevertheless, I live.

24:12.656 --> 24:16.722
And that's what we offer the world

24:17.378 --> 24:21.144
We have the only faith that the world knows that has life.

24:22.306 --> 24:25.832
We have life of it even after death, which is amazing.

24:26.773 --> 24:36.870
I was asked several years ago, by a pastor I admire very much, and he asked me, he said, Jim, I have a question for you.

24:37.812 --> 24:40.416
Would you rather do a wedding or a funeral?

24:40.496 --> 24:44.082
Now this was probably about 15 years ago I was asked this.

24:44.706 --> 24:46.848
He said, would you rather do a wedding or a funeral?

24:46.888 --> 24:48.630
Well, I started to laugh a lot.

24:49.311 --> 24:51.253
And I said, that's funny.

24:52.735 --> 24:54.056
And he said, what would you rather do?

24:55.438 --> 24:59.482
I said, well, I'd rather do a wedding than a funeral.

24:59.542 --> 25:03.086
The pastor looked at me and he said this.

25:03.166 --> 25:04.187
He said, not me, Jim.

25:05.969 --> 25:12.036
I'd rather do the funeral of a believer than do a wedding of two individuals that are believers.

25:12.136 --> 25:13.938
I said, why?

25:14.402 --> 25:16.225
He did kind of give a comical answer.

25:16.285 --> 25:19.150
He said, weddings are the most unreal thing on planet Earth.

25:20.291 --> 25:23.136
And he said, funerals are the most real thing on planet Earth.

25:24.198 --> 25:24.939
And he said this.

25:26.000 --> 25:34.914
He said, the reason why I'd rather do a funeral than a wedding is because the funeral represents the real hope of the Christian.

25:35.676 --> 25:38.460
Unlike any other religion, we have it.

25:39.261 --> 25:42.226
Well, that so, so burned me.

25:43.106 --> 26:08.146
I began to think about, and I tell you what I love to do now, I love to do the gravesite of a believer in Christ, and that we plant the body in the ground, knowing that it's coming up out of that ground one day, and that resurrection, that life that we now have, alive in Christ

26:08.386 --> 26:12.031
was such a great theme in a world that is so dead.

26:12.712 --> 26:17.900
We had the answer and have the answer in a live in Christ.

26:18.360 --> 26:26.732
I love action that had brought to me my takeaway, but life, that Christianity is the faith of life.

26:27.153 --> 26:32.220
We have it for eternal life and we have it for abundant life on this earth.

26:32.240 --> 26:33.522
Now, I is a key letter.

26:34.306 --> 26:38.810
And it's the key to probably brings everything together in this whole theme this year.

26:39.511 --> 26:41.393
And I stands for identification.

26:42.233 --> 26:44.676
We heard a lot of messages on the Holy Spirit.

26:45.156 --> 26:55.746
And if you look at your Romans chapter six passage, instead of the word baptism for just a moment, insert the word identify or identification.

26:55.846 --> 27:00.150
Notice with me, if you would, as we begin to read again, Romans six, verse three.

27:00.931 --> 27:04.114
Know ye not that so many of us as were

27:04.258 --> 27:10.407
identified into Jesus Christ were identified into His death.

27:11.088 --> 27:15.755
Therefore, we are buried with Him by identification into death.

27:16.356 --> 27:24.308
That like as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life.

27:24.388 --> 27:24.888
Look at this.

27:25.249 --> 27:31.378
For if we have been planted together in the likeness of His death, we shall also be in the likeness

27:31.458 --> 27:36.484
of his resurrection, knowing this, that our old man is crucified.

27:36.504 --> 27:37.906
How does all this occur?

27:38.586 --> 27:40.969
It occurs by identification.

27:41.690 --> 27:45.675
Paul wasn't lying when he said, I am crucified with Christ.

27:46.435 --> 27:48.358
He was saying, I'm identified.

27:48.398 --> 27:50.160
Now, how were we identified?

27:50.480 --> 27:53.203
And that's by the work of the Holy Spirit.

27:53.223 --> 27:58.930
And this year, I think some of the best messages Pastor preached all year for me.

27:59.586 --> 28:02.850
were probably the messages on the Holy Spirit.

28:02.870 --> 28:11.042
And understanding that our identification with Christ is through this one who lives inside of us, the Holy Spirit.

28:11.763 --> 28:13.986
And it is through identification.

28:14.006 --> 28:16.609
I always like to give the little illustration, and I didn't get it.

28:16.689 --> 28:19.233
I don't know who taught it to me, but it's not my own.

28:19.774 --> 28:23.619
But before I baptized anybody, I would always use the little wedding ring.

28:24.139 --> 28:28.946
Because I think water baptism, I think someone's getting baptized tonight.

28:29.090 --> 28:35.100
publicly identifying in water baptism with what Christ is did.

28:35.160 --> 28:43.293
Nobody gets saved in that tank of water over there, but they are making a public identification with the death, burial, and resurrection.

28:43.313 --> 28:44.294
Kind of like my wedding ring.

28:44.775 --> 28:51.806
If I take my wedding ring off, which I can't do tonight, but if I take my wedding ring off, I'm still married to my wife.

28:52.708 --> 28:56.754
If I never had worn a wedding ring, I could still have been married.

28:57.186 --> 29:02.875
then why, Jim, do you wear a wedding ring to identify myself as a married man?

29:03.335 --> 29:10.266
You look at the wedding ring, by the way, could a person wear a wedding ring and not be married?

29:10.767 --> 29:11.208
Yes.

29:12.129 --> 29:15.775
So it is the identification of that.

29:15.935 --> 29:19.681
It doesn't mean that a person can get dunked in the tank of water.

29:19.701 --> 29:20.882
It doesn't mean that they're saved.

29:21.483 --> 29:25.810
But it is a picture of identification this year.

29:26.146 --> 29:31.075
The key to alive in Christ is our identification with Christ.

29:31.536 --> 29:32.758
I'm alive with Him.

29:33.640 --> 29:36.185
V stood for victory.

29:37.748 --> 29:43.839
We have now already won and we are already in a position of victory.

29:44.541 --> 29:47.326
Our job now is to claim the victory.

29:47.346 --> 29:49.490
Again, we go back to the book of Joshua.

29:49.666 --> 29:51.829
God had already promised it's yours.

29:52.210 --> 29:53.452
Claim it, Joshua.

29:53.492 --> 29:54.593
Take it.

29:55.014 --> 29:56.516
It's already been given you.

29:56.556 --> 30:03.647
This year, as we so needed, we saw the victory that we have in Jesus Christ.

30:04.928 --> 30:16.946
I had the privilege to preach, I think, three Sunday mornings this year that Pastor allowed me to, and he asked me specifically to speak on a live in Christ.

30:17.026 --> 30:19.570
And one of the areas had to do with victory.

30:19.970 --> 30:28.401
And so often is the case when you study for a message or you preach a message, it speaks more to you than it does usually to the people you preach to.

30:29.202 --> 30:34.770
And that morning it did, and there was a concept that I wanted to get across.

30:35.631 --> 30:42.460
And that week, I think the Lord, I don't know, showed me something, I don't know, but it has really helped me and it's a takeaway for me.

30:43.382 --> 30:49.650
Probably no one in here will remember this, but I started that one of the messages with an illustration

30:50.466 --> 31:20.434
If we were able to take every can in bottle of beer and be able to dispose of every can in bottle of beer, and if we were able to take every can in bottle of liquor in the entire planet Earth and destroy it and get rid of it, would that take care of the alcohol problem on our planet?

31:21.122 --> 31:27.169
No, because we didn't destroy the factories that produce it.

31:28.231 --> 31:41.727
So even though we just went around and took every can of beer, every bottle of beer, every can and bottle of alcohol in the whole world, and we destroyed every one of it, we would still have an alcohol problem on planet Earth.

31:41.767 --> 31:42.107
Why?

31:42.488 --> 31:44.951
Because there's still factories producing it.

31:46.392 --> 31:47.794
And the point is this.

31:49.026 --> 31:54.774
You'll never have victory over sin by just dealing with the results of that sin.

31:55.855 --> 32:00.902
You gotta get to the very basis of it, and that's being alive in Christ.

32:01.783 --> 32:07.531
Seeing who you are in Jesus Christ as your victory over any sin.

32:08.172 --> 32:12.498
You don't take time to, if you're struggling with lust,

32:12.866 --> 32:14.147
Well, don't take time.

32:14.167 --> 32:16.210
God, I have a problem with pornography.

32:16.230 --> 32:17.351
I have a problem with lust.

32:17.651 --> 32:19.333
And Lord, I got to have victory over this.

32:19.393 --> 32:20.895
And all I do is think about it all the time.

32:21.055 --> 32:22.256
We'll stop thinking about it.

32:23.518 --> 32:25.520
The victory's already been given to you.

32:26.161 --> 32:29.644
Live as if you are victorious over it already.

32:30.165 --> 32:36.732
We deal with the cans and the bottles of sin in our life instead of dealing with the factory of where it's produced.

32:37.032 --> 32:40.777
We've got to find ourselves dead to sin and alive to Christ.

32:41.217 --> 32:42.098
This year,

32:42.242 --> 32:45.167
That was life-changing for me and greatly helped.

32:45.187 --> 32:52.940
And then finally, and it really is, kind of sums up the ALIV, and that's experiential, not just doctrinal.

32:54.182 --> 32:59.270
I would imagine in January, when you heard the phrase, alive in Christ, you weren't like, well, what?

32:59.731 --> 33:00.953
It's kind of theoretical.

33:01.634 --> 33:02.896
It's kind of like, what in the world?

33:02.936 --> 33:04.779
This is gonna be a real doctrinal year.

33:05.561 --> 33:08.786
Well, I think our pastor had a goal, and I think he accomplished it.

33:09.378 --> 33:20.276
that made a phrase alive in Christ not be something that is just doctrinal, but something that is experiential, something that we experience and that we live by.

33:20.316 --> 33:24.703
Now I will tell you the greatest illustration that I remember of the whole year.

33:25.624 --> 33:27.467
It's interesting, it wasn't from pastor.

33:28.329 --> 33:29.290
It was from Dean Miller.

33:30.652 --> 33:36.722
And he was here, I believe it was the Sunday that we dedicated the library to the Lord.

33:37.570 --> 33:39.493
And he had a really short time.

33:40.154 --> 33:41.575
I've teased him since then.

33:42.056 --> 33:44.379
I think it was the greatest message I've ever heard of preach.

33:44.399 --> 33:46.102
He only preached 26 minutes, I think.

33:46.682 --> 33:48.224
But I think it was the greatest message.

33:48.285 --> 33:50.007
I said, Dean Miller, take it any way you want.

33:50.027 --> 33:51.649
But I'm just telling you, it was the greatest message.

33:52.410 --> 33:55.835
And he did a phenomenal job of explaining the life in Christ.

33:55.935 --> 34:04.146
And some of you might remember, he closed with an illustration that sometimes you hear something and you go like, that just was amazing.

34:05.378 --> 34:07.141
that he got as a gift.

34:07.321 --> 34:10.947
I think it was from his daughters or from a family member or somebody in the church.

34:11.728 --> 34:15.574
He got a VIP card for car washes.

34:16.756 --> 34:26.090
Now he thought that that VIP car for car washes was that there was an unlimited amount of money on that car.

34:26.811 --> 34:31.058
When he went to the car wash place, there were different car washes that you could get.

34:31.874 --> 34:39.223
And the one was the works and that was they got, they put send in and everything and all they put the smell in it and everything like that.

34:39.563 --> 34:45.811
But he didn't want to get that one because that costs so much and he thought, oh, I don't want to waste all my card.

34:46.091 --> 34:50.897
So I'll just keep getting the exterior, the cheap one, and then I can keep using it.

34:52.159 --> 34:58.386
Late in the year, if I'm not mistaken, it was like November or December, if I remember the story correctly.

34:59.330 --> 35:03.377
He goes in and the owner and the manager was there that day.

35:04.059 --> 35:09.669
He took Dean Miller's card and said, oh, what scent do you want?

35:11.051 --> 35:16.121
And Dean Miller said, well, I'm not sure I got enough money on the card for one of those seven things.

35:16.161 --> 35:17.343
I don't know if there's that much there.

35:19.206 --> 35:21.330
And the manager said, well, you have the VIP card.

35:23.074 --> 35:24.776
You could be getting these every time.

35:24.816 --> 35:26.678
The VIP card has no limit.

35:26.698 --> 35:30.342
You could come in as often as you want and you could get the works every time.

35:31.303 --> 35:40.714
And he said, you telling me that I got all year long and all I just got the outside wash and I could have had the VIP treatment.

35:40.734 --> 35:45.479
Yeah, you could have had the works every time you came in and you could have came in every day this year if you wanted to.

35:46.340 --> 35:47.602
You got the VIP card.

35:49.624 --> 35:51.346
And I remember sitting out there

35:52.514 --> 36:10.366
And I said, oh, Lord, how much of my Christian experience has been on not fully understanding that I am alive in Jesus Christ and that we don't live in the light of what we have in Christ?

36:11.328 --> 36:14.473
Now, I'm excited what pastor's going to show us on January 12th.

36:15.275 --> 36:17.138
I don't even know everything that's going to happen.

36:18.082 --> 36:24.170
And I'm looking forward to the future of our church and the direction that pastor is going to lead us and we're going to get behind it.

36:25.071 --> 36:41.792
But I don't think we should leave 2019 for getting our theme because I think this is one of the most profound spiritual truths in all of our life that we are alive in Christ.

36:42.453 --> 36:46.418
And most of us live like he didn't rise from the tomb.

36:46.946 --> 36:51.712
Most of us struggle with things that we've never seen victory over in our life.

36:52.553 --> 36:58.080
Most of us do not live the victorious Christian life, and we're in the wilderness.

36:58.641 --> 37:01.564
God even miraculously does some things for us.

37:01.624 --> 37:07.752
He brings man unto us, and sometimes he does miracles that our clothes don't wear out or our shoes don't wear out.

37:08.253 --> 37:13.319
God proved himself to the people of Israel, but they weren't where they were supposed to be.

37:13.920 --> 37:15.762
And it gets deceptive sometimes.

37:16.770 --> 37:23.279
Let me ask you, at the end of 2019, are you alive in Christ?

37:24.200 --> 37:25.802
Now, I didn't say were you saved.

37:26.683 --> 37:29.427
You can be a believer and live a defeated life.

37:29.487 --> 37:37.658
The alive in Christ is the key that unlocks our victorious Christian life.

37:38.459 --> 37:44.788
We truly ought to live our lives alive in our risen Savior, Jesus Christ,

